      "patient_summary": "WHAT THIS TRIAL IS TESTING:\nThis study looks at two new drug combinations to see how well they shrink or control non-small cell lung cancer in people with specific genetic markers (EGFR mutations).\n\nWHY THIS MIGHT BE RIGHT FOR YOU:\n* Your specific lung cancer mutation (EGFR exon 19 deletion) is a direct match for what these drugs are designed to target.\n* You have already received some standard treatments, and this trial offers a different approach to managing your cancer.\n* The study is open to people with your stage of lung cancer who are looking for new options.\n\nWHAT WOULD BE INVOLVED:\nYou would receive either a combination of two targeted drugs (amivantamab and lazertinib) or one targeted drug plus chemotherapy. You will need to visit the study site regularly for treatments, check-ups, and scans to see how the medicine is working.\n\nIMPORTANT TO CONFIRM WITH YOUR DOCTOR:\nPlease ask your doctor if you meet the specific requirements for \"measurable lesions\" on your scans. Also, confirm that any side effects from your past chemotherapy have healed enough for you to start a new treatment. Finally, ensure you have not had major surgery in the last four weeks.",
      "physician_brief": "**TRIAL:** NCT06667076; A Study of Amivantamab in Combination With Lazertinib or Chemotherapy for EGFR-Mutated NSCLC; Phase 2; Sponsor: Janssen.\n\n**CLINICAL RATIONALE:** Patient is a 58F with Stage IIIB EGFR Exon 19del+ NSCLC. Following progression on platinum-doublet therapy, this trial offers a targeted approach using the bispecific antibody amivantamab combined with the third-generation TKI lazertinib or chemotherapy, addressing the need for next-line EGFR-directed therapy.\n\n**KEY ELIGIBILITY:** \n*   **Confirmed:** Histology, EGFR Ex19del status, ECOG 1.\n*   **Uncertain:** Requires verification of RECIST v1.1 measurable disease, resolution of prior treatment toxicities to Grade ≤1, and absence of uncontrolled tumor-related pain.\n\n**LOGISTICS:** Site location TBD; requires frequent monitoring for infusion-related reactions and potential ILD.\n\n**RECOMMENDATION:** **Strong Match.** The patient’s molecular profile and prior treatment history align well with the trial’s focus on overcoming resistance in EGFR-mutated NSCLC.",
      "outreach_email": "Subject: Inquiry regarding clinical trial NCT06667076\n\nDear Clinical Trial Coordinator,\n\nI am writing to express my interest in participating in the Phase 2 study of Amivantamab (NCT06667076). \n\nI am a patient currently residing in Boston, MA, diagnosed with Stage IIIB Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer. My tumor is EGFR exon 19 deletion positive with a PD-L1 expression of 40%. My prior treatment includes Carboplatin and Paclitaxel, and I currently maintain an ECOG performance status of 1.\n\nGiven my specific mutation profile and treatment history, I believe I may be a strong candidate for this trial. Could you please confirm if this study is currently enrolling new participants? If so, I would appreciate information regarding the next steps for pre-screening or the process for having my records reviewed.\n\nThank you for your time and for your work in advancing these therapies.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Phone Number]"
